children.label: removeClashingFiles
description:
Removes files that have clashing mappings and cannot be imported together.
Files marked with ERROR clash type will be removed from the file list.

children.label: analyzeFileWithOverrides
description: Creates a function to analyze a file at the specified index with custom overrides.

children.label: index
description: - The index of the file to analyze

returnComment: A function that accepts overrides and performs the file analysis

children.label: getUploadStatus
description: Gets the current upload status including file clashes, analysis status, and import progress.

children.label: getInitializedWithExistingIndex
description: Checks if the file upload manager was initialized with an existing index.
returnComment: True if initialized with an existing index, false otherwise

children.label: getExistingIndexName
description: Gets the name of the existing index being used for import.
returnComment: The existing index name or null if none is set

children.label: setExistingIndexName
description: Sets the existing index name and resets the analysis status.

children.label: name
description: - The index name to set, or null to clear

children.label: isExistingIndexUpload
description: Checks if this upload is targeting an existing index.
returnComment: True if uploading to an existing index, false otherwise

children.label: getFiles
description: Gets the current array of file wrappers being managed.

children.label: updatePipelines
description: Updates the pipelines for all files with the provided array.

children.label: pipelines
description: - Array of pipelines corresponding to each file

children.label: getMappings
description: Gets the current index mappings.

children.label: updateMappings
description: Updates the index mappings configuration.

children.label: mappings
description: - New mappings as object or JSON string

children.label: getSettings
description: Gets the current index settings.

children.label: updateSettings
description: Updates the index settings configuration.

children.label: settings
description: - New settings as object or JSON string

children.label: getAutoCreateDataView
description: Gets whether a data view should be automatically created after import.
returnComment: True if auto-creating data view, false otherwise

description: Removes all convert processors from all file pipelines.
